  "notes": [
    "The bioinformatics minor is intended primarily for bioinformatics tool users who are majoring in a biological or chemical specialty. The bioinformatics minor is also appropriate for computer science or computer engineering majors who are considering graduate work in bioinformatics. The bioinformatics minor cannot be combined with the biomolecular engineering and bioinformatics major. Please visit the Baskin Engineering Undergraduate Experience website to learn more about this minor. PREPARATION FOR THE MINOR BIOL 20A: Cell and Molecular Biology BME 80G/PHIL 80G: Bioethics in the 21st Century: Science, Business, and Society One of the following Chemistry courses: CHEM 3A: General Chemistry OR CHEM 4A: Advanced General Chemistry: Molecular Structure and Reactivity AND CHEM 4AL: Advanced General Chemistry Lab One of the following series: MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics AND MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics OR MATH 11A: Calculus with Applications AND MATH 11B: Calculus with Applications",
    "UC Santa Cruz students may choose to complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and allowable credits. While a minor will appear on a student's official transcript, it will not be listed on their diploma. Pursuing a minor is a personal decision that should align with a student's educational and career goals. Students do not apply for minors when submitting their application to UC Santa Cruz. After enrolling, transfer students interested in pursuing a minor should contact the department offering the minor for guidance."
